Discovery, Kagiso, Shoprite, Truworths: South African Stock Market Preview

-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 
2011-02-22T05:50:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/discovery-kagiso-shoprite-truworths-south-african-stock-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose for the
first day in five, adding 292.64, or 0.9 percent, to 32,806.67
at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.    African Bank Investments Ltd . (ABL SJ): The bank yesterday
announced it will sell 15 million preference shares to selected
investors. The stock gained 40 cents, or 1.1 percent, to 36.79
rand.    Bowler Metcalf  Ltd. (BCF SJ): The plastics manufacturer
sees half-year earnings per share up 26 percent to 38 percent.
Bowler gained 5 cents, or 0.57 percent, to 8.75 rand.    Clientele Ltd . (CLI SJ): The insurer said six-month
headline earnings per share were 26.69 cents versus 23.76 cents.
Its shares remained unchanged at 9.90 rand.    Discovery Holdings Ltd . (DSY SJ): The health insurer
announces first-half results. Discovery gained 22 cents, or 0.6
percent, to 39.78 rand.    Kagiso Media Ltd . (KGM SJ): The publishing company said
interim headline earnings per share were higher at 98.8 cents
per share. Kagiso advanced 15 cents, or 0.9 percent, to 16.40
rand.    Shoprite Holdings Ltd . (SHP SJ): The retailer publishes
first-half earnings. Shoprite jumped 1.94 rand, or 2.1 percent,
to 96.50 rand.    Truworths International Ltd . (TRU SJ): South Africa’s
largest clothing retailer briefs investors on its first-half
earnings. Truworths climbed 1.29 rand, or 2 percent, to 66.79
rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) slipped 1.9 percent to
$25.96. AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) gained 0.5 percent to
$47.55. BHP Billiton Plc (BBL US) dropped 2.9 percent to $77.34.
DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) rose 0.4 percent to $4.62. Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI US) jumped 2.8 percent to $17.29. Harmony Gold Mining
Co. (HMY US) added 1.8 percent to $11.24. Impala Platinum
Holdings (IMPUY US) gained 1.5 percent to $30.19. Sappi Ltd.
(SPP US) fell 0.6 percent to $5.37. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) added
0.4 percent to $51.24.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Franz Wild in Johannesburg at 
